(fifthQuint)Interferon Alfa Plus Sargramostim in Treating Patients With Newly Diagnosed Chronic Phase Chronic Myelogenous Leukemia.

 OBJECTIVES: I.

 Estimate the rate of major cytogenetic responses to sargramostim (GM-CSF) and interferon alfa in patients with newly diagnosed chronic phase chronic myeloid leukemia.

 II.

 Estimate the dosing, schedule, and toxic effects of GM-CSF plus interferon alfa in these patients.

 OUTLINE: All patients are in hematologic remission on subcutaneous interferon alfa upon entering the study.

 Once a complete hematologic response is achieved and the interferon alfa dose has been stable for 14 days, patients receive subcutaneous sargramostim (GM-CSF) daily for 6 months.

 Patients are followed at 3, 6, 9, and 12 months.

 PROJECTED ACCRUAL: Approximately 48 patients will be accrued for this study.

