RATIONALE: Interferon alfa may interfere with the growth of cancer cells.

 Colony-stimulating factors such as sargramostim may increase the number of immune cells found in bone marrow or peripheral blood and may help a person's immune system recover from the side effects of therapy.

 Combining sargramostim with interferon alfa may kill more cancer cells.

 PURPOSE: Phase II trial to study the effectiveness of sargramostim in treating patients who are receiving interferon alfa for chronic phase chronic myelogenous leukemia that is in remission.

